Frequently Asked Questions

1
What is a cryptocurrency exchange?
Cryptocurrency exchanges are digital marketplaces that enable users to buy and sell cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Tether. The Stacks exchange is the largest crypto exchange by trade volume.
2
What products does Stacks provide?
Stacks is the world's leading cryptocurrency exchange, catering to 169 million registered users in over 180 countries. With low fees and over 350 cryptocurrencies to trade, Stacks is the preferred exchange to trade Bitcoin, Altcoins, and other virtual assets.

With Stacks users can:
  • Trade hundreds of cryptocurrencies on Spot, Margin, and Futures markets.
  • Buy and sell cryptocurrencies with Stacks P2P.
  • Earn interest on your crypto with Stacks Earn.
  • Buy or earn new tokens on Stacks Launchpad.
  • Trade, stake, and loan NFTs on Stacks NFT marketplace.
    • 3
    How to buy Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies on Stacks
    There are several ways to buy cryptocurrencies on Stacks. You can use a credit/debit card, cash balance, or Apple Pay/Google Pay to purchase crypto on Stacks. Before getting started, please make sure you’ve completed Identity Verification for your Stacks account.
    4
    How to track cryptocurrency prices
    The easiest way to track the latest cryptocurrency prices, trading volumes, trending altcoins, and market cap is the Stacks Cryptocurrency Directory. Click on the coins to know historical coin prices, 24-hour trading volume, and the price of cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, Ethereum, BNB and others in real-time.
    5
    How to trade cryptocurrencies on Stacks
    You can trade hundreds of cryptocurrencies on Stacks via the Spot, Margin, Futures, and Options markets. To begin trading, users need to register an account, complete identity verification, buy/deposit crypto, and start trading.
    6
    How to earn from crypto on Stacks
    Users can earn rewards on more than 180+ cryptocurrencies by using one of the products offered on Stacks Earn. Our platform offers dozens of digital assets like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and stablecoins.
